76561197991756982,Recommended,215630,16820868,"Posted: 30 June, 2015",all,CerealKiller,"I play RPGs for the story. As long as the controls work and the premise isn't half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ I'm happy. This is very much one of those. If you're looking for a game to blow you away with graphics, or let you roam the world endlessly, this is not the game for you. However, if you enjoy good story-telling and some fun gameplay to go with it, this is a good pit stop. The biggest claim to fame for this game is the DnD type feel. You're never much stronger than your enemies. You have ongoing side plots and decisions you make matter for the future. If you like DnD and RPGs, take this one for a spin. You won't regret it.Only 1 complaint: no fast travel and your movement speed is kinda slow out of combat. Near the end of the game there's a section where you'll ravel over the same area like, 7 times. Put on an audio book.... you'll be briskly jogging a lot."
,Not Recommended,215630,11689767,"Posted: 13 August, 2014",all,Varlarion,"Lot's of lost potential. It is a dark fantasy, linear action RPG with small and not always believable levels. The translation of the complex attribute and talent system of The Dark Eye works well and the skills can be combined for fun battle combos. If you're not familiar with The Dark Eye universe, the story probably makes no sense at all, the (German) voice acting is lacking and the best parts are the storytelling 2D panels in between.Not an entirely bad game, but it could have been so much more."
76561197966515096,Not Recommended,215630,9004322,"Posted: 7 February, 2014",all,Dashu,"The controls are made for consoles and therefore pretty annoying to handle on PC. You can't use half your keyboard and only have 4 potions on shortcut at a time... yeah!The combat ist super easy and extremely boring. It's basically rolling around, spamming left click to beat someone to death and occasionally cast something. Even though I specialized my character into casting spells neither did I have the essence (mana) to cast a lot, it didn't really deal damage either. In the end I found the talent that made me practically an invincible killing machine... didn't get more exciting from there. On the plus side you can finally invest loads of points into non-combat perks and still beat the game. Generally the perks are way more important than passive stats anyway. New dialogue options, better gear, healing people, finding traps, picking locks etc.The story (the reason to play an RPG imho) is... not bad but not really good either. It's a typical ""save my love from a demon"" thing. The visual presentation is a little dull since the characters show little emotion in dialogues. What annoyed me the most was that the story went straight in a direction that was ""choose one of the optionsthat you don't want that screws over your character"" and finally you get blamed for taking decisions you didn't even take. Maybe some of those triggers were faulty. Made the end a lot worse, though."
