oyable to gamers who like lore and journals in games like Dragon Age. the combat is VERY strategic and fun. maybe GoT doesn't have as many character development options but it still has many options for crafting and designing your characters paths.i hate to call any game unplayable, or unnecessary to even try out, but like i said, the lack of a manual save just put it over the edge for me.its basically, a game, with a well thought out character upgrade system, in an ugly static world, with a story that's hard to care about."
